  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Portfolio Manager (Real Estate Finance)",
  "description": "<p>Manage the existing APAC real estate loan portfolio and act as the primary liaison between the Singapore office and their headquarters. You will oversee post-origination matters, allowing the origination team to focus on new business.</p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><ul><li>Portfolio Oversight: Lead day-to-day monitoring of loans, including covenant analysis, rent rolls, valuations, and financial statement reviews.</li><li>Credit Liaison: Partner with credit management in Germany to process amendments, waivers, and monthly performance reports.</li><li>Risk Management: Proactively identify and escalate credit issues, working closely with stakeholders to resolve them.</li><li>Market Intelligence: Conduct APAC market research and provide analytical support (cash flow analysis/property overviews) to the origination team as needed.</li></ul><p>Qualifications</p><ul><li>Experience: 4+ years in real estate finance; hotel sector experience preferred.</li><li>Skills: Strong analytical mindset, meticulous attention to detail, and proactive initiative.</li><li>Communication: Exceptional English proficiency and the ability to manage cross-cultural stakeholder relationships (APAC/Europe).</li></ul><p>To apply online please use the 'apply' function, alternatively you may send an email to j.ong@alsrecruit.com</p><p>(EA: 16S8075/ R2090612)<br /></p>",
